3:28 PM Defendant Alan Alberto Rojas not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Clifford C. Burdon in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
22CM23, 21CT26, 21CT69
Court reviews cases.  
Atty Burdon requests warrant.
BY THE COURT:  Warrant authorized.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 11, 2022 at 02:45 pm.
*Appear for booking to the Marquette County Jail only on 21CT26  *No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license

3:41PM  Defendant Alan Alberto Rojas in court.  Prosecuting attorney Clifford C. Burdon in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
2021CT000026, 2021CT000069 & 22CM23 tracking together:
BY THE COURT:  Warrants quashed in all three cases

Court questions the defendant regarding an interpreter.  Defendant does not need an interpreter.  

Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands and waives his right to an Attorney.  Court finds waiver of attorney made freely, voluntarily & Intelligently. 

Atty Burdon states plea agreement to Count 3 in 22CM23 & Count 2 in 21CT69.  All other counts to be dismissed and read-in.  21CT26 to be dismissed and read-in.  Defendant agrees.

Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Defendant now wants more time to think about it.

BY THE COURT:  Court will set a status on all cases.

BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 Signature bond with conditions on all three cases :
*Appear for booking to the Marquette County Jail only on 21CT26
*No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid drivers license

3:13 PM Defendant Alan Alberto Rojas in court.  Prosecuting attorney Clifford C. Burdon in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
2021CT000026, 2021CT000069 & 22CM23 tracking together:
Court questions the defendant as to why he failed to appear.  Defendant states that he had some personal issues.  Court confirms address.  

Atty Burdon states that he extended an offer to the defendant regarding all three cases in which he would like to accept.  Defendant agrees.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant understands and waives his right to an attorney.  

3:20pm  Recess so the defendant can fill out plea paperwork.

3:40pm  BACK ON THE RECORD:
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 20, 2022 at 03:45 pm.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 20, 2022 at 03:45 pm.
